I""<p>Today, I added Harvard’s Ms. Lat 265 to the SCTA Image Viewer. This manuscript is a witness to Book II of St. Bonaventure’s Commentary on the Sentences of Peter Lombard. It can be viewed here:</p>

<p><a href="http://images.scta.info/?json=5558b135e4b0d557cf926137">http://images.scta.info/?json=5558b135e4b0d557cf926137</a></p>

<p>The ease with which this manuscript was added to the SCTA Image collection is a testament to the power of IIIF.</p>

<p>I found the manuscript here <a href="http://pds.lib.harvard.edu/pds/view/24332177">http://pds.lib.harvard.edu/pds/view/24332177</a>. Then I identified the prepared IIIF manifest here: <a href="http://iiif.lib.harvard.edu/manifests/drs:24332177">http://iiif.lib.harvard.edu/manifests/drs:24332177</a>.</p>

<p>All that was left was to add this to the index.html file of my mirador viewer like so:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$(function() {Mirador({
    "id": "viewer",
    "layout": "1x1",
    "data": [
        ...
        {"manifestUri": "http://iiif.lib.harvard.edu/manifests/drs:24332177"}
    ]
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>and voilà, the 28th manuscript has been added to the collection.</p>

<iframe src="http://images.scta.info/" width="100%" height="400"></iframe>
